<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="78" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="78">
Based on the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath, CA" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="10" pageNumber="81" pagination="295 - 310" title="Indian Macropsinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). II. Species described by W. L. Distant and descriptions of new species from the Indian subcontinent." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/187631281794709791" volume="12" year="1981">Viraktamath (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, this species can be separated from other members of the subgenus mostly by the following features: the pygofer ventral margin has two spine-like processes distally, the tapered aedeagal shaft has an excavated distal margin in middle formed into a U-shaped in caudal view, and the dorsal connective has a bifid apex and caudally-directed triangular process from its inner ventral margin.
</paragraph>
